1. UI Layer (Presentation Logic)

Purpose: Handles the user interface and presentation logic.
Technologies Mentioned:

Angular
React


Role: This layer is responsible for rendering the front-end and interacting with the API layer to display data to users.


2. API Layer (Business Logic)

Purpose: Acts as the middle layer between the UI and the database. It contains the business logic and exposes APIs for communication.
Technologies Mentioned:

Java Struts
.NET Core
Python Flask
Python Django
Express.js


Role: Processes requests from the UI, applies business rules, and interacts with the database layer.


3. Database Layer (Data)

Purpose: Stores and manages application data.
Databases Mentioned:

Oracle
MongoDB
MySQL
MSSQL
Postgres


Role: Provides persistent storage and responds to queries from the API layer.


Flow of Data

UI Layer → API Layer → Database Layer
The UI sends requests to the API layer, which processes them and interacts with the database to fetch or store data.

